HEADWORD: Cleistogamous
<hw>Cleis*tog"a*mous</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ closed (fr. <?/ to
shut) + <grk>ga`mos</grk> marriage.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Having, beside the usual flowers, other minute, closed flowers,
without petals or with minute petals; -- said of certain species of
plants which possess flowers of two or more kinds, the closed ones being
so constituted as to insure self-fertilization.</def>
<rj><au>Darwin.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

